§. 1. The highest Immunities I ever met with, ascribed to Conscience are in Bishop Saunderson, a most Zealous stickler for Ceremonies. Serm. on 14. Rom, 23. There cannot (says he) be imagined a higher contempt of God then for a Man to despise the power of his own Conscience, which is the highest under Heaven, as being Gods most immediate Deputy for the Ordering his life, and ways; 

